David Goodwin wrote:
> 
> The last message reminds me that there are a couple of things I don't
> think I have announced yet.
> 
> 1.  There is now some documentation for the Cantera Python interface.
> Go to the main Cantera page (http://www.python.org), then follow the
> link 'Documentation' to 'Documented Python Code'
> It is still a work in progress, but provides a reference for the
> various methods available ini each class.
> 
> 2.  This is really a preannouncement --- 1D flames are coming to
> MATLAB!  I will release an update next week that will allow doing 1D
> flames in MATLAB, including stagnation-point flames, and hopefully
> freely-propagating and opposed-jet flames (premixed or not).  Should be
> available by next Wednesday or so; maybe sooner.  Stay tuned...
> 
> dg
